headlines.description: — Celtics coach Joe Mazzulla has a team rule that everybody contests shots, even after the whistle. Players, coaches -- everybody.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown, Tatum combine for 63 points as Celtics overwhelm Suns for 2nd time in a week, 127-112

headlines.description: — Whether he was burying his shots or moving the ball, Paul George seemed to make all the right decisions. The Clippers will sure take more of that.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paul George nails 6 3s, scores 28, Kawhi Leonard adds 27 points as Clippers beat Bulls 126-111

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored a season-high 37 points as the Houston Rockets built a big lead early and cruised to a 135-119 win over the Washington Wizards on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green scores season-high 37 points as Rockets get 135-119 win over Wizards

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 32 points and 11 rebounds to lead the Milwaukee Bucks past the Philadelphia 76ers 114-105 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis Antetokounmpo scores 32 points to lead the Bucks to a 114-105 win over the 76ers

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 31 points and nine rebounds to help the Oklahoma City Thunder defeat the short-handed Dallas Mavericks 126-119 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 31 to lead Thunder past Doncic-less Mavericks 126-119

events.name: New York Knicks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 45 points and the New York Knicks rolled past the Portland Trail Blazers, 105-93 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 45 points and the Knicks roll past the Trail Blazers, 105-93
